result.execSummary:
This case has not been concluded. Unless a judgment of conviction is entered, the defendant is presumed innocent of all charges.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
Court calls @ 3:39 PM/ RM 203. Defendant Donald Curtis Jueck Jr. appeared by video, in custody in Langlade County Jail.  Attorney Elizabeth R. Gebert in court for State of Wisconsin, via zoom. Court notes alleged victim is present in courtroom. Court reviews case history and appointment of counsel report. Def. continues to wish for counsel. Court also calls 22CM102, to track along. State has complied with victims rights. Bond continues.
Adjourned initial appearance scheduled for November 14, 2022 at 01:30 pm.

Court calls @ 3:08 PM, 22CF188 & 22CM102. Defendant Donald Curtis Jueck Jr. appeared by video, in custody in Langlade County Jail.  Attorney Kelly Hays in court for State of Wisconsin, via zoom. Def. has contacted PD Office and does qualify. Def. continues to wish for counsel. Court advises Def. of right to have a P.H. within time limits and questions if Def. would like to waive time limits. Def. would like to waive time limits and wait for counsel. Court accepts waiver of time limits and finds good cause. Bond continues.
Adjourned initial appearance scheduled for October 24, 2022 at 01:30 pm.

Maintain Absolute Sobriety. 
No presence in establishments with Class B liquor license. 
No contact with victim in 22CF188 file. 
Defendant to apply with Public Defender within 7 days at 715-536-9105.

Court calls @ 1:26 PM/ RM 203, 22CF188 & 22CM102. Defendant Donald Curtis Jueck Jr. appeared by video, in custody in Langlade County Jail.  Attorney Kelly Hays in court for State of Wisconsin, via zoom. Def. has copies of complaints, advised of charges and penalties. Def. given Atty rights and given 4 options, PD, hire own, court appointed Atty. or represent self. Def. does wish to attain counsel. Defendant to apply with Public Defender within 7 days at 715-536-9105. State is in compliance with victim rights. Victim is present in courtroom accompanied by victim witness coordinator. Court questions if State would like them to address witness. State confirms. Victim gives statement regarding bail bond. State gives bail bond recommendations and requests $10,000.00 cash bond to cover both files, with conditions to Maintain Absolute Sobriety, No presence in establishments with Class B liquor license, No contact with victim in 22CF188 file and No illegal use or possession of controlled substances. Def. gives bail bond argument and requests signature bond. Court has reviewed criminal complaints and considers bail bond factors. Court orders $10,000.00 cash bond in 22CF188 with conditions to Maintain Absolute Sobriety, No presence in establishments with Class B liquor license, No contact with alleged victim and Defendant to apply with Public Defender within 7 days at 715-536-9105. Court orders 1,000.00 signature bond on 22CM102 with no monetary conditions.
Adjourned initial appearance scheduled for October 10, 2022 at 01:30 pm.
